In 1992 the Drug Enforcement Agency began secretly tracking phone calls to 116 countries on a drug trafficking watch list . 
  The program was approved by President George H . 
 W . 
  Bush in the final months of his presidency . 
  The DEA monitored every phone call made from the U . 
 S . 
  to the countries on the list . 
  It was used to infiltrate drug trafficking rings . 
  The system was used for nearly two decades before being shut down in 2013 . 
 